        "text": "Life after divorce, says Melinda Gates, \"has been wonderful\".\n\nMelinda (59) and billionaire Microsoft founder Bill Gates (69) officially announced the end of their 27 year marriage in August 2021.\n\nGoing through the divorce, she said, was “hard” and “painful,” but now that it’s behind her, life has turned out for the better.\n\nAfter the divorce, Melinda's net worth was reportedly nearly $7 billion (R127m), and she donated about $1bn of that to charity.\n\nIn an interview with Time magazine, the philanthropist revealed she and Bill had been separated and taking turns living in their marital home since the start of the pandemic, long before they publicly announced their divorce.\n\n“It gave us the privacy to do what needed to be done in private.\n\n“You know, I separated first before I made the full decision about a divorce. And to be able to do that in private while I’m still trying to take care of the kids, while still making certain decisions about how you’re going to disentangle your life – thank God.”\n\nThe pair met when Melinda joined Microsoft as a product manager in 1987. A year later they started dating and tied the knot in 1994. They have two daughters, Jennifer (28), Phoebe (21) and a son, Rory (23).\n\nAs one of the richest couples in the world they established the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, which funds IT education in the US as well as healthcare and poverty upliftment initiatives around the world.\n\nThe decision to end their marriage wasn't easy, said Melinda.\n\n“I thought a lot about my three children. And I certainly thought about the effect on the [Bill & Melinda Gates] Foundation. I wanted to make sure when we came through it, that all of those pieces were intact.\""
